                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.51/252</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-26T11:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 26, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My telegram of July 24, noon. Congress accepted veto and House passed new measure
                    satisfactory to President except that tax on iron and copper too high. He hopes
                    to get Senate pass same bill before adjournment that is imminent, and will
                    suspend part of iron and copper tax expecting reduction by Congress next
                    winter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
